Hosp rate vs pm2.5

Linda Zhou

12/15/2018

library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(splines)
library(gridExtra)
PH_pollution <- read.csv("~/Downloads/PH_data/PH_pollution.csv")
city = filter(PH_pollution, denom > 2000)
city_AZ = filter(PH_pollution, zipcode %in% 85001:85086 | zipcode %in% 85701:85775)
makeplot = function(dat, pm, rate){
        ggplot(dat, aes(pm, rate)) + 
        geom_point(size = 1) + geom_smooth(method = "lm", formula = y~ns(x,df=3))+
                theme_bw(base_size = 7)
}
g1 = makeplot(city,city$pm25, city$cases/city$denom)+labs(title = "pm25 vs case in denom>2000")
g2 = makeplot(city,city$pmcoarse,city$cases/city$denom)+labs(title = "pmcoarse vs case in denom>2000")
g3 = makeplot(city,city$pm25,city$primary/city$denom)+labs(title = "pm25 vs primary in denom>2000")
g4 = makeplot(city,city$pmcoarse,city$primary/city$denom)+labs(title = "pmcoarse vs primary in denom>2000")
g5 = makeplot(city_AZ,city_AZ$pm25,city_AZ$cases/city_AZ$denom)+labs(title = "pm25 vs case in Pheonix&Tucson")
g6 = makeplot(city_AZ,city_AZ$pmcoarse,city_AZ$cases/city_AZ$denom)+labs(title = "pmcoarse vs case in Pheonix&Tucson")
g7 = makeplot(city_AZ,city_AZ$pm25,city_AZ$primary/city_AZ$denom)+labs(title = "pm25 vs primary in Pheonix&Tucson")
g8 = makeplot(city_AZ,city_AZ$pmcoarse,city_AZ$primary/city_AZ$denom)+labs(title = "pmcoarse vs primary in Pheonix&Tucson")
grid.arrange(g1,g2,g3,g4,g5,g6,g7,g8,ncol = 3)

#handle missing data
city_pm2.5 = ifelse(is.na(city$pm25),1,0)
missing1.glm = glm(city_pm2.5 ~ ns(Latitude, df = 3) + ns(Longitude, df = 3), 
                   family=binomial(link='logit'), data = city)
Pr_missing_city = predict(missing1.glm, type='response')
PH_pollution_city = cbind(city,Pr_missing_city)

#indicator pm25 > 15, pmcoarse > 20
indicator1 = ifelse(city$pm25>=15,1,0)
indicator2 = ifelse(city$pmcoarse>=16,1,0)

#pm2.5
pm25_city.glm = glm(primary ~ offset(log(denom)) + pm25 + hs_orless + pov + urc +
                            pm25:indicator1, family='quasipoisson', 
                    data = PH_pollution_city, weights = 1/(1-Pr_missing_city))

#pmcoarse
pmcoarse_city.glm = glm(cases ~ offset(log(denom)) + pmcoarse + hs_orless + 
                            pov + urc + pmcoarse:indicator2, family = 'quasipoisson',
                    data = PH_pollution_city, weights = 1/(1-Pr_missing_city))
summary(pm25_city.glm)

So,

no positive correlation in major cities of Arizona.

if specify denom > certain amount, we can observe a positive correlation between pmcoarse and cases/primary.

when pm2.5>15, pmcoarse>16, there are significant increases of hospitalization rate.

but the model fits poorly for pmcoarse/pm2.5 vs cases. (4632.9 on 1057 degrees of freedom)
